  48:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     This header file declares the interface to some inline macros
  49:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     handling the watchdog timer present in many AVR devices.  In order
  50:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     to prevent the watchdog timer configuration from being
  51:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     accidentally altered by a crashing application, a special timed
  52:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     sequence is required in order to change it.  The macros within
  53:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     this header file handle the required sequence automatically
  54:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     before changing any value.  Interrupts will be disabled during
  55:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     the manipulation.
  56:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h **** 
  57:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     \note Depending on the fuse configuration of the particular
  58:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     device, further restrictions might apply, in particular it might
  59:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     be disallowed to turn off the watchdog timer.
  60:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h **** 
  61:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     Note that for newer devices (ATmega88 and newer, effectively any
  62:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     AVR that has the option to also generate interrupts), the watchdog
  63:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     timer remains active even after a system reset (except a power-on
  64:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     condition), using the fastest prescaler value (approximately 15
  65:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     ms).  It is therefore required to turn off the watchdog early
  66:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     during program startup, the datasheet recommends a sequence like
  67:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h ****     the following:
  68:/usr/local/Cellar/avr-gcc/8.3.0/avr/include/avr/wdt.h **** 
